August 2019 School Board Meetings Rescheduled

The Tuesday, August 20th, 2019 school board regular and organizational meetings have been rescheduled and will now take place on Wednesday, August 28th, 2019. The organizational meeting will begin at 8am with the regular meeting starting upon the conclusion of the organizational meeting (8:15am). The meetings will be held at the International Academy of Saginaw, 1944 Iowa Ave., Saginaw, MI 48601. Please call 989-921-1000 for further information.

post_text:
The International Academy of Saginaw is seeking applications for an upcoming vacant position on its Board of Directors. An individual will be appointed to fill the position on July 1st, 2019.

Interested persons must submit a letter expressing interest in the board position and their qualifications for the position to the Academy’s Deputy Director no later than 3:00p.m. on Friday May 17th, 2019.
Following a review of the submitted materials, the board will schedule interviews with selected candidates. Not all candidates for the vacancy will be interviewed.

If you have any questions concerning the role of the Board of Directors and the responsibilities of a board member, please contact Kandi Thomas, Deputy Director, at 989-921-1000.

If you have any questions concerning the role of the Board of Directors and the responsibilities of a board member, please contact Kandi Thomas, Deputy Director, at 989-921-1000.

INTRODUCING the all new IAS Referral Program

Do you know a family looking for a new school for their student(s)? Refer them to IAS and WIN!

If you refer a new family to enroll at IAS, your registered student(s) will receive a free uniform polo shirt (to be handed out at Meet Your Teacher Night and/or the 1st day of school.

PLUS, if the new student(s) remains registered through October 31st, YOU and the new parent will both be entered into a drawing for a new TV! Two drawings - one for existing parents and one for new parents who participate in the referral program. ONE ENTRY PER NEW STUDENT! Winners announced at Parent/Teacher Conferences in early November.

Any questions, be sure to contact us! 989-921-1000 or IAS@sabis.net.

New families should reference the referral program and your name when registering their student(s) with Ms. Guerra.

Applications available online at ias.sabis.net/enrollment/online-form

Do you ever buy items that have Boxtops on them? We are collecting them here at IAS! There is a container on the front desk or you can have your child bring them in to their teacher to turn in . Boxtops are on many products including: Cocoa Puffs cereal, Go-Gurt, Chex cereal, Old el Paso tortillas, Fruit Gushers, Scott Towel 6 pack, and more. Help us raise money for field trips with box tops. Last year, we raised enough money for busses for 2 of our field trips. #wildcatstyle

BOXTOPS4EDUCATION.COM
Collection Drive
